Farcaster, a decentralized social network built on Ethereum, is redefining how users interact online by prioritizing user ownership and interoperability. Among its innovative features, Farcaster supports mini apps—compact web applications that integrate seamlessly into its ecosystem, enhancing user experience with tools like authentication, notifications, and wallet interactions. One standout mini app making waves is Tipn, a platform that introduces a novel micro-tipping system to reward creators and foster community engagement. This article dives into Tipn, exploring its functionality, impact, and role in Farcaster’s decentralized social landscape.

